(226, 12, 'Design of GaN based optical modulator with mach-zehnder interferometer structure', 'WSEAS Transactions on Communications', 'Attica', NULL, 'Greece', '2014', 'Desember', 'Int', 'tin', 'In this work we have designed a Mach Zehnder interferometer (MZI) for electro optic modulator at telecommunication wavelength using GaN on Sapphire. The knowledge of GaN sample optical properties were also investigated, resulting refractive index for the GaN layers were found to be nTE=2.279±0.001 and nTM = 2.316±0.001 and good temperatur stability. Optimization of the structure parameters and electrodes required for this structure was conducted accurately by theoretical tools using BPM methods. The results showed possibility to realize GaN based MZI for future optical modulator devices', '12_karyatulis_wseastransactionsoncommunications_f52f0d4c.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(227, 12, ' High coverage ZnO nanorods on ITO susbtrates via modified chemical bath deposition (CBD) method at ', ' Advanced Materials Research', 'Baech', NULL, 'Switzerland', '2013', 'September', 'Int', 'tin', 'In the present work, ZnO nanorods array were successfully grown on ITO substrate via chemical bath deposition method (CBD). The seeding solution was prepared at low temperature (0°C) using zinc nitrate tetrahydrate and hexamethylenetetramine. The as-deposited ZnO nanorods were hexagonal wurtzite structure growing vertically on the substrate. Various reaction times from 3 to 5 hours were applied upon the CBD process at 90°C. The results showed that the duration of reaction time has affected the nanorods array properties. With the increase of reaction time from 3 to 5 hours has increased the diameter and crystallite size of nanorods from 325 to 583 nm, and from 22.68 to 34.28 nm. As a result, the band gap energy, Eg of ZnO nanorods decreased from 3.63 to 3.13 eV.', '12_karyatulis_advancedmaterialsresearch_347c65f3.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(228, 12, 'Optical Properties of Gallium Nitride Heterostructures Grown on Silicon for Waveguiding Application', ' Advanced Materials Research', 'Baech', NULL, 'Switzerland', '2014', 'Juni', 'Int', 'tin', 'Gallium nitride (GaN) on silicon (Si) is governed by the possibility to use this family of semiconductor for novel optoelectronic devices. GaN layers are deposited by MOCVD on silicon Si (111) using AlGaN buffer layer. We have studied the microstructure quality of the films. From SEM, TEM and AFM observations, we have observed that the films exhibit a good quality: the films are highly oriented (0001) with a smooth surface morphology (roughness of 12nm). We have completely characterized the optical properties using the prism coupling technique.', '12_karyatulis_advancedmaterialsresearch_c5dd15d6.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(229, 12, ' A simple optimization of triple-junction solar cell ncSi:H/a-  Si:H/a-SiGe:H using computer modelin', ' Advanced Materials Research', 'Baech', NULL, 'Switzerland', '2014', 'Februari', 'Int', 'tin', 'We report for the first time a simple optimization of triple-junction solar cell nc-Si:H/a-Si:H/a-SiGe:H using computer modeling and Robust Design. Firstly we performed a computer modeling of solar cell by wxAMPS software. Subsequently, we investigated the parameters of the solar cell layers and the effect of the solar cell efficiency using Robust Design via Taguchi method, ANOVA and additive model. The results show that the a-Si:H middle absorber cell has the highest contribution of solar cell efficiency at 40.87% and the nc-Si:H n-back layer cell has the second highest contribution of solar cell efficiency at 31.15%. Moreover, the optimum condition for triple-junction solar cell is A2 B1 C2 D2 with solar cell efficiency at 15.73%. These results indicate that Robust Design succeeded predicting the best condition for optimizing triple-junction solar cell nc-Si:H/a-Si:H/a-SiGe:H.', '12_karyatulis_advancedmaterialsresearch_64a2ccda.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(230, 12, ' Maskless localized patterning of biomolecules on carbon nanotube microarray functionalized by ultra', 'Applied Physics Letters ', 'Melville', NULL, 'USA', '2016', 'Juli', 'Int', 'stin', 'Ultrafine plasma jet is a promising technology with great potential for nano- or micro-scale surface modification. In this letter, we demonstrated the use of ultrafine atmospheric pressure plasma jet (APPJ) for patterning bio-immobilization on vertically aligned carbon nanotube (CNT) microarray platform without a physical mask. The biotin-avidin system was utilized to demonstrate localized biomolecule patterning on the biosensor devices. Using ±7.5 kV square-wave pulses, the optimum condition of plasma jet with He/NH3 gas mixture and 2.5 s treatment period has been obtained to functionalize CNTs. The functionalized CNTs were covalently linked to biotin, bovine serum albumin (BSA), and avidin-(fluorescein isothiocyanate) FITC, sequentially. BSA was necessary as a blocking agent to protect the untreated CNTs from avidin adsorption. The localized patterning results have been evaluated from avidin-FITC fluorescence signals analyzed using a fluorescence microscope. The patterning of biomolecules on the CNT microarray platform using ultrafine APPJ provides a means for potential application of microarray biosensors based on CNTs.', '12_karyatulis_appliedphysicsletters_2522f6c2.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(231, 12, 'Maskless functionalization of a carbon nanotube dot array biosensor using an ultrafine atmospheric p', 'Carbon', 'Lexington', NULL, 'USA', '2015', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'stin', 'To realize maskless functionalization of a carbon nanotubes (CNTs) dot array, a localized surface functionalization technology using an ultrafine atmospheric pressure plasma jet was developed. The plasma surface functionalization onto vertically aligned CNTs was carried out in two stages: pretreatment for activation of the CNT surface and posttreatment for surface functionalization. The experimental results of chemical derivatization with the fluorescent dye show that the CNT dot array was not only successfully functionalized with amino (–NH2) and carboxyl (–COOH) groups but also functionalized without any interference between functional groups. The success of maskless functionalization in the line pattern provides a means of a multifunctionalized CNT dot array with direct implications for future application of a microarray biosensor.', '12_karyatulis_carbon_18e9c828.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(232, 12, ' III-nitride semiconductors based optical power splitter device design for underwater application', ' International Journal of Electrical and Computer Engineering', 'Yogyakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2018', 'Oktober', 'Int', 'tin', 'In this paper, we introduce III-nitrides based 1× 4 optical power splitter for underwater optical communication applications. To the best of our knowledge, this is a first study for the design of multimode interference (MMI) and four-branch taper waveguide based on GaN/sapphire. The microstructure of GaN semiconductor grown by Metalorganic Chemical Vapor Deposition (MOCVD) on (0001) sapphire reported. The numerical experimental is conducted using the 3D FD-BPM method. The results showed that the optical power splitter has an excess loss of 0.013 dB and imbalance of 0.17 dB. The results open the opportunity for the future device using this technology for the underwater application.', '12_karyatulis_internationaljournalofelectricalandcomputerengineering_af2aafaf.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(233, 12, 'A Simple Three Branch Optical Power Splitter Design based on III-Nitride Semiconductor for Optical T', 'IJTech', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2016', 'Desember', 'Int', 'tin', ' We propose a simple design of 1×3 optical power splitter which uses gallium nitride (GaN) on sapphire. The design consists of widely used large cross section input rib waveguide, a rectangular multimode interference (MMI) structure, and three-branch rib waveguides. The MMI structure is selected since their attractive performances, such as compactness, low excess loss, wide bandwidth and ease to fabricate. The power splitter is designed for the third telecommunication window, i.e.,  = 1.55 μm. Optimization of the geometrical structure parameters for the design is conducted theoretically utilizing 3D FD-BPM method. It is found that the power splitter exhibits excess loss of 0.46 dB and imbalanced of 0.001 dB at  = 1.55 μm for = 2.279 and =2.316, respectively. It means that there is a potential application of the proposed GaN based power splitter structure in the future.', '12_karyatulis_ijtech_c34b17f6.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(234, 12, ' Morphological and structural study of vertically aligned zinc oxide nanorods grown on spin coated s', 'IJTech', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2019', 'Januari', 'Int', 'stin', 'In this study, vertically aligned zinc oxide (ZnO) nanorod (NR) arrays were grown with the 2-step method. Spin coating was used to apply the seed layer, and by increasing the number of repetitions (n), higher thickness of the seed layer was achieved. The effects of different seed layer thicknesses, spin coated at different rotational speeds (v) and how the variables (v and n) influence the morphological and crystal properties of the resulting ZnO NRs were analyzed. The effects of 1, 3, and 5 (n), with (v) of 3000 or 4000 rpm were investigated, and the formed seed layers were characterized by using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and X-ray diffraction (XRD) profiles. The ZnO NR arrays were grown by a chemical bath deposition method because of its simplicity and ease of use. Full width at half maximum (FWHM) analysis was conducted on the XRD chart and Raman spectrum to analyze the grain size and Wurtzite distortion of the ZnO NRs. A lower FWHM value was attributed to the lower number of structural disorders in the ZnO NRs, which equated to the most stable or structured Wurtzite structures in the ZnO NRs, achieved at the lowest FWHM value. The lowest FWHM for (002) XRD peak was obtained at 0.35° for ZnO NRs grown with a seed layer spin coated at 4000 rpm once. The crystallite size calculated by Scherrer’s equation gave a size of 25.14 nm. The lowest FWHM for E2(High) Raman peak was obtained at 6.00 cm–1 for ZnO NRs grown with a seed layer spin coated at 4000 rpm three times.', '12_karyatulis_ijtech_bd64daa6.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(235, 12, 'Growth of Zinc Oxide Nanorods with the Thickness of Less than or Equal to 1 μ m through Zinc Acetate', ' Journal of Engineering', 'London', NULL, 'United Kingdom', '2019', 'November', 'Int', 'stin', 'Arrays of zinc oxide (ZnO) nanorod (NR) were fabricated in a vertical axis direction through the two-step method of seed layer’s deposition and growth of the NR. The seed layer was applied by spin coating with a three-time repetition (n) and rotational speed () at 3000 rpm. After the seed layer had grown, ZnO NRs were grown with a growth solution made by combining one zinc source with one hydroxide source. There were two different zinc sources, i.e., zinc acetate dehydrate and zinc nitrate hexahydrate and, for comparison, zinc acetate (ZA) and zinc nitrate (ZN) were each combined with the same hydroxide source, hexamethylenetetramine (HMT). Later, the growth solutions were processed by the chemical bath deposition (CBD) method using a waterbath machine. The CBD method was started at room temperature until it reached the designated temperature at 85°C. At that point, the growth time was calculated from the zero-minute condition. It was found that ZnO NRs had already grown at a thickness of about 100 nm for both ZA and ZN sources. The growth time varied at 15, 60, 90, and 120 minutes after the zero-minute point. By using two separate and independent zinc sources while growing ZnO NRs at various growth periods, several ZnO NRs’ thicknesses were controlled. According to a paper by Lee et al., the lower thickness of ZnO NRs boosted the charge transfer properties of perovskite solar cells (PSCs) because the series resistance between ZnO/perovskite interfaces was lessened. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) images were observed to analyze the morphological shape of the ZnO NRs. X-ray diffraction (XRD) profiles were characterized to obtain the data for ZnO NR crystallinity. Full width at half maximum (FWHM) analysis was performed at the (002) ZnO peak to calculate the crystal size of the peak. From the results, the smallest crystallite sizes for ZnO NRs grown from ZA and ZN sources were 10.70 nm and 19.29 nm, respectively, which would be the most suitable condition for PSC application.', '12_karyatulis_journalofengineering_e6884255.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-06 10:02:52', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(236, 12, 'Design of a Four-Branch Optical Power Splitter Based on Gallium-Nitride Using Rectangular Waveguide ', 'Journal of Engineering', 'London', NULL, 'United Kingdom', '2019', 'Juli', 'Int', 'stin', 'This paper reports design of a simple four-branch optical power splitter using five parallel rectangular waveguides coupling in a gallium-nitride (GaN) semiconductor/sapphire for telecommunication links. The optimisation was conducted using the 3D FD-BPM method for long wavelength optical communication. The result shows that, at propagation length of 925 μm, the optical power input was successfully split into four uniform output beams, each with 24% of total input power. It is also shown that the relative output power distribution is almost stable through the C-band range. At the operating wavelength of 1.55 μm, the proposed power splitter has an excess loss lower than 0.2 dB. This study demonstrates the opportunity to develop optical interconnections from UV-Visible to near IR wavelengths.', '12_karyatulis_journalofengineering_67c9c972.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(237, 86, 'New Market New Opportunity', 'Inovastra 34', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2018', 'Februari', 'Nas', 'stin', '1.	UT dan Komatsu memperkenalkan unit excavator elektrik dan Studi kelayakan dan benchmark ke Thailand \r\n2.	UT Membantu PT Bukit Asam dalam proses akusisi anak perusahaan dan develop anak perusahaan tersebut dengan progran end to end solution\r\n3.	UT berusaha keras untuk memenangkan tender pengadaan unit pada PT Bukit Asam dengan bundling Full Manintenance Contract.\r\n4.	UT melaksanakan project Costomer Solution Management (End to End Solution ) pada PT Bukit Asam\r\n', '86_karyatulis_inovastra34_24cb3767.pdf', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-27 00:50:10', '2022-10-25 17:00:00'),
(238, 12, 'Effect of Annealing on Characterization of TiO2-Based DSSC', 'Journal of Materials Science and Engineering A', ' Warsaw', NULL, 'Polandia', '2012', 'Februari', 'Int', 'stin', 'One of the most important parameter that affects Dye-Sensitized Solar Cell (DSSC) characteristics is porosity. There are many aspects that can influence the porosity such as particles size of titanium-dioxide (TiO2), annealing temperature and processing parameter or fabrication itself. In this paper, one of important parameter will be discussed, i.e., effect of annealing on characterization of TiO2 thin layer. First the TiO2 thin film was formed on indium tin-oxide (ITO) glass by stir casting process using doctor balde to make thin layer on ITO glass, second the thin film was annealed at different temperature start from 100 °C, 150 °C, 200 °C, 300 °C and 350 °C for 30 min. The samples then were characterized both microstructural analysis and electrical properties. It is found that annealing at 200 °C was optimum condition due to porosity content of 32% which has good in electrical properties such as fill factor, conductivity, open-circuit voltage (Voc) and short-circuit current (Isc), respectively.', '12_karyatulis_journalofmaterialsscienceandengineeringa_c475499d.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(239, 12, 'An optical power divider based on mode coupling using GaN/Al2O3 for underwater communication', 'Photonics, MDPI', 'Basel', NULL, 'Switzerland', '2019', 'Juni', 'Int', 'ren', 'This paper details the design of a 1 × 8 optical power divider, using a gallium nitride (GaN) semiconductor on sapphire, which can be applied to underwater optical wireless communication. The design consists of nine parallel rectangular waveguides which are based on mode coupling phenomena. Analysis of the design was performed using the beam propagation method (BPM). The optimization was conducted using the 3D finite difference (FD)-BPM method with an optical signal input at the wavelength required for maritime application of λ = 0.45 µm. The signal was injected into the central waveguide. The results showed that at a propagation length of 1480 µm the optical power is divided into eight output beams with an excess loss of 0.46 dB and imbalance of 0.51 dB. The proposed design can be further developed and applied in future underwater communication technology.', '12_karyatulis_photonicsmdpi_4b1fa872.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2048, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(240, 12, 'Divais Fotonika Berbasis Galium Nitrida Teori Dan Desain', 'UI Publising', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2019', 'Desember', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Dalam buku ini disampaikan tinjauan teori dan cara mendesain divais fotonika berbasis galium nitrida, di samping juga contoh-contoh hasil desain untuk jaringan telekomunikasi.', '12_karyatulis_uipublising_c9cb9794.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(241, 12, 'Biochip Sensor Berbasis Carbon Nanotube (Fabrikasi, Fungsionalisasi, dan Immobilisasi) ', 'deepublish', 'Yogyakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2019', 'Agustus', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Buku ini menulis tentang Fabrikasi, Fungsionalisasi, dan Immobilasasi Biochip Sensor berbasis Carbon nanotube ', '12_karyatulis_deepublish_74c09619.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-04 17:00:00', '2022-10-04 17:00:00'),
(242, 12, 'Solar Cell', 'Intechopen', 'London', NULL, 'United Kingdom', '2010', 'November', 'Int', 'stin', 'Solar cell is the most potential energy source for the future, due to its characteristics of renewable and pollution free. However, the recent technology still does not achieve high Watt/m2 and cost efficiency. Solar cell technology still needs to be developed and improved further to obtain optimal efficiency and cost. Moreover, in order to analyze and develop the solar cell technologies, it is required the understanding of solar cell fundamental concepts. The fundamentals how the solar works include 2 phenomena, i.e.: (1) Photonics electron\r\nexcitation effect to generate electron-hole pairs in materials and (2) diode rectifying.', '12_karyatulis_intechopen_4ee530b8.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(243, 12, 'Solar Cell Si/Si0,7Ge0,3 Menggunakan Metoda Step Graded pada Pertumbuhan Lapisan Si0,7Ge0,3', 'Jurnal Kajian Teknologi, Fakultas Teknik Universitas Tarumanegara', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2005', 'Mei', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Using Si0.7Ge0.3  alloy at silicon solar cell is one method for increasing silicon solar cell efficiency because\r\nSi0.7Ge0.3 has lower bandgap than silicon. By adding this lower bandgap it can improve absorption capability\r\nand current collection also increase. Besides for reducing misfit dislocation defects at Si/Si0.7Ge0.3 junction it had been growth by step graded. Those defects were the result on the lattice constant different between silicon and germanium. The step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer, which is used at silicon solar cell, is the 3 step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer with Si0.725Ge0.275 layer and Si0.72Ge0.25 layer growth on silicon layer, respectively before Si0.7Ge0.3 layer had been done. In this paper it had been analyzed the effect of step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer toward silicon solar cell efficiency with simulation\'s software PCID version 5.8 (Donald A Clugston, 1997), which is written for IBM-compatible personal computers and used for solving the fully coupled nonlinear equations for the quasi-one-dimensional transport of electrons and holes in crystalline semiconductor devices, with emphasis on photovoltaic devices. Parameters, we are investigated, were short circuit current, open circuit voltage, fill\r\nfactor. Those three parameters will affect the efficiency of silicon solar cell. The simulation had been performed\r\nalso to the silicon solar cell without Si0.7Ge0.3 and the silicon with non graded Si0.7Ge0.3. As the result silicon\r\nsolar cell efficiency increase from 15.01% without Si0.7Ge0.3 layer and 24.4% with Si0.7Ge0.3 layer without step\r\ngraded to 25.41%with step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer.', '12_karyatulis_jurnalkajianteknologifakultasteknikuniversitastarumanegara_195ca51a.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(244, 12, 'Pemodelan Heterojunction Bipolar Transistor Silikon Germanium (HBT-SiGe) dengan 3D QUASI-Simulator', 'Jurnal P&PT, Asosiasi Politeknik Indonesia', 'Bandung', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2010', 'Juni', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Penelitian ini membahas pemodelan Heterojunction Bipolar Transistor Silikon-Germanium (HBT-SiGe) dengan menggunakan simulator 3D quasi simulator. ', '12_karyatulis_jurnalpptasosiasipoliteknikindonesia_43a46451.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(245, 12, 'Implementasi Tata Letak VLSI pada Perancangan Prosesor FFT Untuk N=2', 'Jurnal Teknologi FTUI', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '1997', 'Maret', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Transformasi Fourier merupakan salah satu contoh dari teknik analisa transformasi, yang digunakan\r\nuntuk menyederhanakan solusi dari suatu masalah komputasi. Transfarmasi Fourier dari sebuah gelombang\r\ndiperlukai untuk memisahkan gelombang tersebut menjadi sejumlah gelombang sinusoidal dengan frekuensi\r\nyang berbeda. Sebuah algoritma yang efisien, yaitu suatu Transformasi Fourier Cepat (Fast Fourier Transform -\r\nFFT) telah dikembangkan.FFT ini digunakan untuk menghitung DFT (Discrete Fourier Transform). Dengan\r\ndemikian telah terjadi perubahan yang besar dalam menganalisa berbagai cabang llmu Pengetahuan (science).\r\nProsesor FFT yang terkecil mempunyai dua titik transformasi (N=2).\r\nPada penelitian ini dibahas tentang implementasi tata letak VLSI pada perancangan prosesor FFT untuk titik transformasi sebanyak dua buah (N=2). Implementasi ini dilakukan pada kertas milimeter dan hasilnya dianalisa secara teoritis.', '12_karyatulis_jurnalteknologiftui_255a7519.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(246, 12, 'Analisa Simulasi VLAN di Gedung Kantor Pusat PT. X', 'Jurnal Teknologi FTUI', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2002', 'September', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Dalam makalah ini akan dianalisa perbandingan performansi bentuk koneksi dan pemakaian\r\nbandwidth dari jaringan eksis dan simulasi VLAN (Virtual Local Area Network). proses perbandingan\r\ndilakukan dengan menggunakan bantuan Network Analyzer & Management System Sniffer pro untuk\r\nmenunjukkan grafik waktu nyata kondisi suatu jaringan yang dipantai, meliputi: packet/s, Broadcast/s\r\ndan Utilization%. Berdasarkan data hasil uji coba diperoleh kinerja jaringai eksis dan kinerja simulasi\r\nVLAN. Data hasil uji coba tersebut, selaniutnya akan dianalisa untik menentukan performansi jaringan\r\nyang meliputi bentuk koneksi dan peningkatan efisiensi bandwidth. Hasil analisa menunjukkan, simulasi\r\nVLAN memiliki bentuk koneksi yang lebih baik dibandingkan dengan jaringan eksis, ,selain itu simulasi\r\nVLAN juga meningkatkan efisiensi bandwidth jaringan eksis.', '12_karyatulis_jurnalteknologiftui_68087188.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(247, 12, 'Karakteristik Lapisan Graded Si1-xGex Pada Solar Cell Silikon', 'Jurnal Teknologi FTUI', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2004', 'September', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Si1-xGex, merupakan bahan yang potensial untuk meningkatkan efisiensi solar cell silikon. Bahan ini \r\ndapat menyerap tidak hanya spektrum cahaya tampak (visible light), tetapi juga spektrum cahaya inframerah yang tldak dapat diserap oleh bahan silikon. Dengan kemampuan penyerapan tersebut, bahan Si1-xGex, digunakan untuk meningkatkan efisiensl solar cell silikon. Untuk mengurangi cacat  misfit dislocation pada persambungan Si-Si1-xGex, maka penumbuhannya dilakukan secara bertahap (step graded) berdasarkan fraksi mol (x) dari lapisan Si1-xGex. Cacat ini terjadi akibat adanya perbedaan lattice constant antara bahan silikon dan germanium. Lapisan step graded Si1-xGex yang digunakan pada solar cell silikon adalah 3 step gradedd Si1-xGex\r\ndengan x: 0,275; 0,28 dan 0,3', '12_karyatulis_jurnalteknologiftui_ee6bd9ac.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(248, 12, 'Optimization and Analysis of Al0,85Ga0.15As/GaAs Heteroface Homojunction Thin-Film Solar Cell', 'Jurnal Teknologi FTUI', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2005', 'Agustus', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Untuk mengoptimasikan unjuk kerja sel pada aplikasi PV ruang angkasa, maka pada makalah ini ditambahkan lapisan window Al0,85Ga0,15As pada sel surya thin-film GaAs. Perancangan sel surya thin-film yang menggunakan substrat glas  dengan ketebalan film secara keseluruhan hanya 9, 79 I µm; merepresentasikan intensitas bahan yang sangat efektif, oleh karena itu memerlukan biaya yang murah  tanpa mengurangi unjuk kerja sel . Perancangan  sel surya dilakukan dengan simulasi menggunakan alat Bantu perangkat Iunak PC1D versi 5.6 dan menggunakan iluminasi AM0. Dengan menggunakan lapisan BSF, permukaan bertekstur piramida, dan deposisi ARC, sel surya yang dirancang mencapai efisiensi 17,97% dan telah dibuktikan sebagai sel surya ideal untuk implementasi ruang angkasa dengan menunjukkan keluaran arus hubung singkat stabilitas tinggi sel\r\nsurya sebesar 35,54 mA/cm2.\r\n', '12_karyatulis_jurnalteknologiftui_60be7320.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(249, 12, 'Perancangan Pengendali Faktor Daya Untuk Listrik Rumah', 'Jurnal Teknologi FTUI', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2006', 'September', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Pengendali faktor daya untuk penggunaan listrik rumah adalah alat yang secara otomatis mengendalikan faktor daya untuk tetap bernilai satu atau mendekati nilai\r\nsatu dan hanya dapat digunakan pada jaringan listrik satu fase skala penggunaan rumah tangga dengan cara menghitung pemakaian beban listrik,  tegangan listrik dan faktor daya sebleum dikompensasi\r\nsecqra terus menerus untuk menentukan besarnya nilai kapasitansi yang harus digunakan sebagai kompensator beban induktif. Dalam makalah ini dirancang dan dibuat pengendali  faktor  daya untuk penggunaan listrik rumah berfase tunggal, 220V/50H2, daya maksimum 2200VA yang mompu mengendalikan  faktor daya jala-jala listrik tetap berada dalam  jangkah mendekati I.', '12_karyatulis_jurnalteknologiftui_9353cc27.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-06 08:08:45', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(250, 12, 'Design of gan-based low-loss y-branch power splitter', 'Makara Journal of Technology', 'Depok', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2014', 'Desember', 'Nas', 'tin', 'We present a Y-branch power splitter design with a multimode section using GaN on Sapphire at telecommunication wavelength. The GaN sample optical properties were also investigated, resulting in a refractive index for the GaN layers nTE=2.289±0.001 and nTM=2.324±0.00. Optimization of the structure parameters for this structure was conducted accurately using BPM methods. The results demonstrated the possibility of realizing a GaN-based Y-branch power splitter for various applications.', '12_karyatulis_makarajournaloftechnology_e9edf77f.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-06 09:39:40', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(251, 12, 'Analisis Cel surya Si/Si1-xGex Dengan Optimalisasi Ketebalan Lapisan Step Graded Si1-xGex', 'Majalah Ilmiah Teknik Elektro (MITE)-ITB', 'Bandung', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2003', 'Desember', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Si1-xGex alloy is one of the promising candidates for increasing silicon solar cell efficiency. This alloy absorbs visible light and also near infrared light spectrum. The absorption of insolation by the step graded Si1-xGex layer solar cell, is affected by the thickness an the fraction mole (x) and its absorption coefficient. Further, it influences the efficiency of the solar cell. In this paper we investigate an analyze the effect of the thickness of the step graded base layer by using simutaion’s tools, i.e. PC1D version 5.8. We include parameters, that refer to the efficiency of the Si/ Si1-xGex silicon solar cell; the open circuit voltage, the short circuit current, and the fill factor. By using the step graded Si1-xGex layer, the dislocation defect, due to the difference of lattice constant between Si and SiGe, decrease. In simulation we used combination of the fraction mole (x) is x(2)=0.3, x(3)=0.28 and x(4)=0.275. Results show that the optimal combination of the step graded Si1-xGex layer thickness are; W(2)=0.00062 m, W(3)=0.9808 m and W(4) = 0.013 m and achieve the optimal open circuit voltage, short circuit current and FF.', '12_karyatulis_majalahilmiahteknikelektromiteitb_185eb5e7.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 16, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3072, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(252, 12, 'The design of respiratory monitoring system based on laser reflection for infant incubator', 'Proceedings of the International Symposium of Biomedical Engineering (ISBE 2018) (AIP Conference Pro', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2018', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'tin', 'We proposed the design of a respiration system based on laser reflection for an infant incubator that is able to continuously operate. The device consists of a laser diode (λ=650 nm; P=5 mW), a paper reflector, photodiode array as a detector, comparator, microcontroller Arduino UNO R3, and LCD. Also, there is a buzzer for anticipating emergency situations such as apnea. It utilizes the reflection of laser light on paper reflector attached to an infant simulator. Next, the reflection will be received by photodiode array and comparator which connects to the Arduino UNO R3. Then, the result was displayed on an LCD. From the experiment results, it was indicated that the system could measure respiratory rate from 10 up to 70 breaths per minute with an error of 2.357%.', '12_karyatulis_proceedingsoftheinternationalsymposiumofbiomedicalengineeringisbe2018_2ced6e2a.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-06 10:04:54', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(253, 12, 'The design of stethoscope-based heart rate monitoring device for infant incubator application', 'Proceedings of the International Symposium of Biomedical Engineering (ISBE 2018) (AIP Conference Pro', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2018', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'tin', 'The design of stethoscope-based heart rate monitoring device for infant incubator applications was reported in this paper. This device utilizes a stethoscope as a heartbeat sensor which was placed on the incubator mattress. This heartbeat signal was then processed by a signal-conditioning electronic circuit. After that, the output was processed by an Arduino Uno microcontroller before being displayed on an LCD in the form of BPM (beat per minutes). The device is also equipped with a buzzer to indicate the absence of a heartbeat. The measurement results showed that the device could measure heartbeats from a baby’s back with a 3.23% possibility of error.', '12_karyatulis_proceedingsoftheinternationalsymposiumofbiomedicalengineeringisbe2018aipconferenceproceedings2019_30e270b5.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(254, 12, 'Design of portable electrocardiography (ECG) based on capacitive electrode', 'Proceedings of the International Symposium of Biomedical Engineering (ISBE 2018) (AIP Conference Pro', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2018', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'tin', 'The heart is one of the most vital organs in the human body that pumps blood. Therefore, it is very important to monitor the condition of the heart. The condition of a human heart can be diagnosed by measuring the heart rate frequency (beats per minute). We propose a design of a portable electrocardiography (ECG) based on capacitive electrodes for heart rate monitoring. The device consists of electrodes attached to a plastic sheet which is placed on a mattress bed under a patient’s back. Before being processed by Arduino UNO microcontroller, the output signal of the electrodes is processed using signal-conditioning circuit consisting of instrumentation-amplifier circuit, filter, and non-inverting amplifier. The signal processing results obtained from the conditioning circuit are displayed on the LCD screen. The test results show that the QRS complex signal can be clearly detected. Various thickness of the patient cloth also produces different values. With this factor taken into account, cottons with varying thickness (from 0.2 mm up to 0.8 mm) are used to measure the heart rate signals. Measurements with varied cotton thickness shows that the thicker the clothing material is, the weaker and more fluctuative the cardiac signal read by the capacitive ECG design will be. To test the accuracy of the proposed design, the measurement result is compared to ECG PM 10 which is a commonly used device for heart rate monitoring. It shows that experiment on different subjects result in an average error of 0.435%. Based on the Association for the Advancement of Medical Instrumentation (AAMI)’s standard of maximum error (5%), the error rate of the proposed device is still within the range of tolerance.', '12_karyatulis_proceedingsoftheinternationalsymposiumofbiomedicalengineeringisbe2018aipconferenceproceedings2019_d922b118.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(255, 12, 'Development and analysis characteristic solar powered system on lapan surveillance UAV 03 (LSU 03)', '2nd Engineering Physics International Conference 2018 (EPIC 2018) (AIP Conference Proceedings 2019)', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2018', 'November', 'Int', 'tin', 'We are developing a solar powered system (SPS) on LAPAN Surveillance UAV - 03 (LSU-03). It is developed for marine monitoring to support marine security from illegal fishing. A longer time is needed to optimize the monitoring missions. This is strongly supported by Indonesia’s sunlit lands throughout the year so long-distance targets and wide area coverage can be achieved. The total power required is 96 Watts per hour. Therefore, it is very important to fulfill the power to fly for 6 hours. The solar powered system consists of solar module, maximum power point tracking (MPPT), and battery. The system development is to regenerate the power. A hardware design and terrestrial measurement of SPS is presented. It was conducted in Aeronautics Technology Center – LAPAN, Bogor. According to the results, the development of solar powered system gave 12.76 percent efficiency. The I-V graphics and battery charging time is presented. The SPS was able to charge the battery 8 Ah for 60 minutes. Therefore the SPS satisfy the power requirement for LSU-03 onboard electrical system.', '12_karyatulis_2ndengineeringphysicsinternationalconference2018epic2018aipconferenceproceedings2019_c1078f2e.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(256, 12, 'Si/Si0.7Ge0.3 Solar Cell by Optimally Thickness of graded Si0.7Ge0.3 Layer', 'The 2nd ASEAN Science Congress and Sub Committee on Non Conventional Energy Research (SCNCER) 2005 ', 'Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2005', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'tin', 'The thickness of graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer will affect the absorption of solar light on the solar cell system. By increasing the absorption of solar light, achieved by lowering the thickness, this will increase the efficiency of solar cell device. Furthermore, optimum thickness graded-Si0.7Ge0.3 layer will contribute in economic aspect; on the other hand, this effort should not decrease the functioning of device itself. Consequently, reducing thickness of the cell will decrease the short circuit current. This can be prevented by using the lower-band gap material in the active base region of the cell. The potential candidate is SiGe alloy. In this paper we optimized the thickness of graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer in order to minimize the defect dislocation due to the difference of lattice constant between Si and SiGe and also increase the efficiency of solar cell device. We investigate and analyze the effect of changing the thickness of graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer by using simulation’s tools, i.e. pc1d version 5.8, and report the performance of this device, especially open circuit voltage, short circuit current, and fill factor which will affect the efficiency of device. In this paper, we will compare the performances of Si solar cell with graded-Si0.7Ge0.3, bulk Si0.7Ge0.3, and without Si0.7Ge0.3 layer.', '12_karyatulis_the2ndaseansciencecongressandsubcommitteeonnonconventionalenergyresearchscncer2005_cbec4db6.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(257, 12, 'The Si1-xGex Layer on GaAs/Si Solar Cell', 'Brunei International Conference On Engineering And Technology (BICET) 2005', 'Brunei Darussalam', NULL, 'Brunei Darussalam', '2005', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'tin', 'For converting solar radiation to electrical current it can be used solar cell with conversion efficiency as high as possible.  At this paper we propose the Si1-xGex layer which is utilized as the buffer layer of the GaAs/Si solar cell. The Si1-xGex layer we applied contents from 10% to 80 % germanium (silicon-like).We investigate and analysis the effect of the Si1-xGex layer by using simulation’s tools, i.e. pc1d version 5.8, and the functioning of this device, especially open circuit voltage, short circuit current, fill factor which will affect the efficiency of device.', '12_karyatulis_bruneiinternationalconferenceonengineeringandtechnologybicet2005_ee223bc0.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(258, 12, 'Development of Automatic Plasma Functionalization System Based on Atmospheric Pressure Plasma Jet', 'International Conference on Electrical Engineering and Computer Science (EECS) 2015 ', 'Hong Kong', NULL, 'Hong Kong', '2015', 'Desember', 'Int', 'tin', 'An atmospheric pressure plasma jet (APPJ) is an effective plasma technology for surface modification due to technically simple and great potential for nano- or micro-scale modification. In this study, we show the recent research progress to develop automatic plasma functionalization system based on APPJ. Automatic micro-scale functionalization was successfully conducted by synchronizing the APPJ plasma treatment and computer-controlled X-Y stage.', '12_karyatulis_internationalconferenceonelectricalengineeringandcomputerscienceeecs2015_4b070632.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(259, 12, 'Effect of Graded Si1-xGex Layer On Silicon Base Layer Solar Cell', 'Engineering and Technology Conference (EnTech) 2003', 'Serawak', NULL, 'Malaysia', '2003', 'Agustus', 'Int', 'tin', 'Because of their superior performance compared to conventional silicon devices we used the graded Si1-xGex layer for increasing the efficiency of solar cell device. We investigate and analysis the effect of graded Si1-xGex layer by using simulation’s tools, i.e. pc1d version 5.8. We also analyze the magnitude of x (fraction mole), which determine such as energy gap, lattice constant   of   material.   The graded Si1-xGex layer we applied contents from 10% to 80 % germanium (silicon-like). We assume that the defect dislocation, due to the difference of lattice constant between Si and SiGe, could be reduced if we growth SiGe in grading.  Results show that the fill factor, short circuit current and open circuit voltage increase by using graded Si1-xGex layer on silicon base layer solar cell so the efficiency of cell also improved. This is compared to SiGe/Si solar cell without grading on SiGe layer.', '12_karyatulis_engineeringandtechnologyconferenceentech2003_e78b0c1d.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(260, 12, 'Optical Properties of Gallium Nitride Heterostructures Grown on Silicon for Waveguiding Application', 'International Association of Computer Science and Information Technology (IACSIT) Conference 2014', 'Sarawak', NULL, 'Malaysia', '2014', 'Juni', 'Int', 'tin', 'Gallium nitride (GaN) on silicon (Si) is governed by the possibility to use this family of semiconductor for novel optoelectronic devices. GaN layers are deposited by MOCVD on silicon Si (111) using AlGaN buffer layer. We have studied the microstructure quality of the films. From SEM, TEM and AFM observations, we have observed that the films exhibit a good quality: the films are highly oriented (0001) with a smooth surface morphology (roughness of 12nm). We have completely characterized the optical properties using the prism coupling technique.', '12_karyatulis_internationalassociationofcomputerscienceandinformationtechnologyiacsitconference2014_728d78d8.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00'),
(261, 12, 'Effect of the Particle Size and Lifespan of Activated Carbon-Based Electrode on the Performance of P', '2020 2nd International Conference on Electrical, Control and Instrumentation Engineering (ICECIE)', 'Kuala Lumpur', NULL, 'Malaysia', '2020', 'November', 'Int', 'tin', 'Perovskite solar cells (PSCs) studies focus on low-cost material deployment in the present time. The best performance of PSC to convert light energy into electricity is PSC that employing gold (Au) as the counter electrode (CE), which is an expensive material. Carbon becomes the best alternative material to replace Au as CE, which is a low-cost material. On the other side, carbon has a work function of 5.0 eV near the work function of Au (5.1 eV). Carbon also a diversity material according to the atom bonds that dividing carbon into several allotropes. Activated carbon derived from biological material is one of carbon\'s allotropes that only a few researches deploying activated carbon as CE. Therefore, in this research, the effect of particle size and lifespan of the activated carbon-based electrode to PSCs performance will be investigated. The fabrication procedure and measurement process of PSCs production with an activated carbon-based electrode is described in this paper. Carbon with the particle size of mesh 1000 and lifespan of 0 days exhibit the best performance, which is produced V OC of 1.28 volt; I SC of 8.04 mA; FF of 0.512; and power conversion energy (PCE) of 2.85%.', '12_karyatulis_20202ndinternationalconferenceonelectricalcontrolandinstrumentationengineeringicecie_d129217d.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-10-05 17:00:00', '2022-10-05 17:00:00');
