(344, 100, 'AE REMOTE SURVEY \"Survey Pengambilan Data Engineering Jarak Jauh\"', 'PT United Tractors Tbk', 'DKI Jakarta', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2020', 'September', 'Lok', 'tin', 'Awal Pandemic pada pertengahan Maret 2020, seluruh permintaan survey lapangan di cancel dan beberapa job yang sudah jalan di stop. Hal ini sangat menggangu stabilitas pekerjaan di Application Engineering PT United Tractors Tbk untuk melaksanakan support kepada Customer. Sehingga dibuat methode survey dengan kolaborasi Application Engineering HO (Jakarta) dengan team PT United Tractors Tbk Cabang dan Site. Jadi support kepada customer tetap bisa dilaksanakan meskipun mobilitas terbatas karena kebijakan pandemic covid-19.\r\n', '100_karyatulis_ptunitedtractorstbk_1381d403.pdf', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-27 17:00:00', '2022-10-27 17:00:00'),
(345, 111, 'STUDI KOMPARASI BEBERAPA TEKNIK UNTUK MENURUNKAN ARUS INRUSH MAGNETISASI TRAFO MENGGUNAKAN SOFTWARE ', 'SKRIPSI TEKNIK ELEKTRO UGM', 'YOGYAKARTA', NULL, 'INDONESIA', '2010', 'Oktober', 'Nas', 'sed', 'Arus inrush magnetisasi trafo adalah problem yang belum sepenuhnya terpecahkan saat ini. Beberapa teknik berhasil ditemukan untuk menurunkan arus inrush. ', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-27 17:00:00', '2022-10-27 17:00:00'),
(346, 111, 'PENILAIAN KONDISI TRANSFORMATOR DAYA BERDASARKAN DATA ANALISIS GAS TERLARUT DAN DATA KARAKTERISTIK M', 'THESIS TEKNIK ELEKTRO ITB', 'BANDUNG', NULL, 'INDONESIA', '2018', 'Juni', 'Nas', 'tin', 'Transformator daya merupakan komponen penting dalam jaringan transmisi dan distribusi. Dari pengalaman para ahli di bidang pemeliharaan trafo, sulit untuk menentukan apakah trafo beroperasi secara normal atau tidak jika trafo tersebut tidak memiliki riwayat pemeliharaan dan riwayat gangguan yang cukup.', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-27 17:00:00', '2022-10-27 17:00:00'),
(347, 111, 'Applications of ANFIS to Estimate the Degree of Polymerization Using Transformer Dissolve Gas Analys', 'Polymer Sciences Journal ISSN: 2471-9935', 'Brussel', NULL, 'Belgia', '2018', 'Juli', 'Int', 'tin', 'Degree of Polymerization is a reliable parameter that can identify the health condition and remaining operational life of the paper insulation within power transformers. Measuring this parameter is a challenging process due to the difficulty in acquiring paper samples from hot spot locations of operating transformers. Insulation oil characteristics and dissolved gas analysis (DGA) of power transformers have become powerful tools to overcome this limitation, because these tests are regularly performed by utilities in Indonesia, unlike furfural and degree of polymerization measurements. This paper presents a novel Adaptive Neuro Fuzzy Inference System (ANFIS) approach to estimate the paper degree of polymerization based on dissolved gas analysis and oil characteristics. In this context, data of oil insulation characteristics, DGA, and furan compounds of 200 150/20 kV and 42 500/150 kV operating transformers are collected from PT. PLN (Persero). The Calculated degree of polymerization from furan data of each investigated transformer is analyzed using the corresponding oil insulation characteristics and DGA data. Results show that carbon oxides compounds, acidity number, interfacial tension, and colour of the oil are statistically correlated with the degree of polymerization of the insulation paper. Parameters that highly correlated with the degree of polymerization are used as input parameters to the proposed ANFIS model to estimate the degree of polymerization value. The results of the developed ANFIS model reveal an overall accuracy more than 86% for the two investigated transformers’ data. The accuracy of the proposed ANFIS model can be enhanced through tuning the model using future obtained results.', '111_karyatulis_polymersciencesjournalissn24719935_cb87f932.pdf', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-27 17:00:00', '2022-10-27 17:00:00'),
