(86, 17, '2019-02-01', '2020-02-01', 'UNIVERSITAS INDONESIA', 'Ketua ', 'Evaluasi Biomekanik\'ferhadap Posisi Dan Pergerakan OtotTangan Manusia Dalam Berahtivitas', 'HIBAH - SKEMA PITTA-B-UNIVERSITAS INDONESIA', 'DEPOK', 'DEPOK', 'Indonesia', 'smp3', 'anggota', 'Rp. 0.00', 'BESAR', 'sed', 'stin', 'tin', 'The hand is the upper limb in the human body that has motor functions and plays an important role in \r\ncarrying out daily activities. Almost all human activities are carried out by hand. A person\'s expertise \r\nin carrying out an activity, especially one using hands, is called dexterity. In Indonesia, writing \r\narmchair with desktop fixed at the right side is a common product used at tertiary education level \r\nwhich is uncomfortable for left-handed students because they have to tilt their body awkwardly to the \r\nright side. During learning activity, students spend hours a day using laptop with its portable design \r\ncan lead to a higher potential risk of musculoskeletal disorder (MSD) in neck area because the screen \r\nheight is lower than recommended causing prolonged neck flexion. Related to MSD, Job \r\ncharacteristics in the garment industry are generally material-handling processes involving machinery \r\nwith high repetition that can cause Work-related Musculoskeletal Disorder (WMSD).', '17_pengkerja_universitasindonesia_ketua.pdf', 'W.2.1.1, W.2.2.2, W.2.3.2., W.2.4.2., W.2.5.1., W.3.1.1., W.4.1.1., W.4.2.4., W.4.3.7., W.4.4.2., P.6.1.5., P.6.2.3., P.7.1.6., P.7.2.7., P.10.1.1., P.11.2.3.', 16, 48, 0, NULL, 768, 768, 768, 768, '2022-11-04 09:45:19', '2022-11-03 17:00:00'),
