(96, 17, '2020-02-17', '2021-02-17', 'UNIVERSITAS INDONESIA', 'Ketua ', ' Perancangan Strategi Peningkatan Penggunaan Utilisasi Platform E-Learning  di Universitas Indonesia', 'HIBAH - UNIVERSITAS INDONESIA', 'DEPOK', 'DEPOK', 'Indonesia', 'smp3', 'anggota', 'Rp. 0.80', 'BESAR', 'dik', 'tin', 'tin', 'Abstract (100-250 words) \r\n\r\nThe era of digitalization encourages the development of information technology. Based on the Global Digital report (2019) made by We Are Social and Hootsuite\'s, the total penetration of internet users in Indonesia reached 56%. This shows a very rapid change and continues to grow.\r\nThis change occurs in various fields, one of them is the Education. The result from the adoption of technology information in the field of education brought some significant changes and stimulates the adoption of methods of distance learning, which is e-learning, a form of direct result of the integration of education and utilization of technology and it is considered to have become a platform that is very influential in the world of education ( Al-Fraihat, Joy, & Sinclair, 2017).\r\nIn 2016, a research was conducted by McGraw Hill Education and found that 81% of students in the United States agree that digital learning technology helps them improve their grades. But ironically, in 2019 the Minister of Research Technology and Higher Education (Menristekdikti) confirmed that from the total of 4,741 Higher Education Institutions in Indonesia, only around 15-20 universities had implemented e-learning in their educational institutions.\r\n	Based on a study conducted by Clay, Rowland & Packard in 2009, it was stated that the success of the acceptance and application of e-learning tools was determined by the eagerness of students in adapting and accepting the technology that was implemented on an ongoing basis or not. This phenomenon then becomes crucial, especially in developing countries. As in Indonesia, for example, readiness for acceptance of technological changes at higher levels of education is still low. The development of technology-based learning media is being strongly supported by the government, but its actual usage is still not optimal. This study will analyze from a holistic aspect with objectives to increase the utilization of e-learning platform in University of Indonesia, which includes analyzing the factors that can increase continuance intention in several scientific clusters, deciding which content and information that should be provided by e-learning media, and conducting studies to analyze the factors that can influence the intentions of lecturer in using e-learning platforms thus from this study will able to give recommendations and strategies for increasing continuance intention both for students and lecturer in University of Indonesia.', '17_pengkerja_UNIVERSITASINDONESIA_Ketua.pdf', 'W.2.1.1, W.2.2.2, W.2.3.2., W.2.4.2., W.2.5.1., W.3.1.1., W.4.1.1., W.4.2.4., W.4.3.7., W.4.4.2., P.6.1.5., P.6.2.3., P.7.1.6., P.7.2.7., P.10.1.1., P.11.2.3.', 16, 48, 0, NULL, 768, 768, 768, 768, '2022-10-14 08:54:12', '2022-10-13 17:00:00'),
