(226, 12, 'Mak', 'Design of Application Warehouse Management System Based on RFID', 'The 4th Indonesia Japan Joint Scientific Symposium 2010 ', 'Universitas Indonesia - Chiba University', 'Bali', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2010', 'Oktober', 'Int', 'tin', 'Identification technology based on radio frequency (Radio Frequency Identification - RFID) has evolved. The technological evolved is triggered by a great need for applications to automate the identification of various service industries, purchasing, distribution logistics, the flow of goods and inventory. This paper introduces the application of RFID at level middleware for Warehouse Management System based on RFID. Moreover, this paper also designs hardware and software for entering warehouse to improve efficiency.', '12_seminar_the4thindonesiajapanjointscientificsymposium2010_45cdc903.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6144, NULL, '2022-09-25 17:00:00', '2022-09-25 17:00:00'),
(227, 12, 'Mak', 'Design of GaAs/Si Solar Cell with Graded Si0.9Ge0.1 Layer', 'The 4th Indonesia Japan Joint Scientific Synposium 2010', 'Universitas Indonesia - Chiba University', 'Bali', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2010', 'Oktober', 'Int', 'stin', 'Solar cell can be used  for converting solar radiation to electrical current with conversion efficiency as high as possible. At this paper we propose the graded Si0.9Ge0.1 layer which is utilized as the buffer layer of the GaAs/Si solar cell. The problem associated with this method is that, because the growth of Si0.9Ge0.1 layer on silicon layer cause misfit dislocation, it will also reduce the current generation. Due to this reason we use the graded Si0.9Ge0.1 layer in order to reduce misfit dislocations. Those defects are the result on the lattice constant different between silicon and germanium. The graded Si0.9Ge0.1 layer, we applied, is 10% germanium contents (silicon-like). We investigate and analysis the effect of the graded Si0.9Ge0.1 layer by using simulation’s tools, i.e. pc1d version 5.8, and the functioning of this device, especially open circuit voltage, short circuit current, fill factor which will affect the efficiency of device. ', '12_seminar_the4thindonesiajapanjointscientificsynposium2010_3903969d.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(228, 12, 'Mak', 'Stability of Perovskite Solar Cell with Optimized CuSCN as Hole Transport Layer', '2018 5th IEEE International Conference on Engineering, Technologies & Applied Sciences (ICETAS)', 'AIT Conference Center Bangkok', 'Bangkok', NULL, 'Thailand', '2018', 'November', 'Int', 'stin', 'Perovskite material has extensively investigated in several years due to its ability as solar cell active layer. However, stability of perovskite solar cell is still a challenge for mass production and commercialization. Transport layer is one of concern to overcome the stability problem. Inorganic material such as CuSCN can be use as p-type transport layer and more robust from degradation compared to organic transport layer. Furthermore, CuSCN has excellent transparency, low-cost and simple fabrication, and high hole mobility. In this research, we use CuSCN as hole transport layer and deposited it using spin coating method. Optimized CuSCN layer was obtained by varied spin coating rotational speed. Afterwards, the completed devices were studied its stability. The result is, performance of optimized solar cell was degraded about 50% from its initial measurement after 14 days.', '12_seminar_20185thieeeinternationalconferenceonengineeringtechnologiesappliedsciencesicetas_96721415.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(229, 12, 'Mak', 'Effect of Perovskite Precursors Molarity on Solar Cell Performance', '2019 11th International Conference on Information Technology and Electrical Engineering, ICITEE 2019', 'Faculty of Information Technology, King Mongkut\'s Institute of Technology Ladkrabang', 'Pattaya', NULL, 'Thailand', '2019', 'Oktober', 'Int', 'stin', 'Solar cell is a very new renewable power supply and it still in the development process. Especially with the perovskite-based solar cell (PSC) which in recent year it shows a very high potential of being very efficient power. It has not been the most efficient but the increase or its efficiency percentage is exponentially increasing. In this work, we want to find the most efficient molarity for PbCl 2 . We were using the spin coating and annealing method to make layers of material on top of FTO glass. This method is very simple and easy to use. The PSC structure consists of 6 layers, namely FTO glass, Electron Transfer Material (ETM), Perovskite, Hole Transfer Material (HTM), carbon, and FTO glass. Perovskite on this solar cell is the active layer where this layer will generate electron and hole when it is shined by sunlight. The probability of electron-hole generation will be increased by the more particle of precursors in this active layer. The molarity of precursors of this layer affects the amount of its particle and will raise the performance of the solar cell. From the fabrication results by varying the molarity, it was found that the perovskite-based solar cell with 0.5M of PbCl 2 is best molarity value with much less PbCl 2 and MAI needed to make it which save more material, and with the highest result of the performance of the PSC, namely 0.56V V oc , 2.37mAI sc , and 0.33 fill factor.', '12_seminar_201911thinternationalconferenceoninformationtechnologyandelectricalengineeringicitee2019_e87e1697.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(230, 12, 'Mak', 'Band-gap optimization for improvement Cu(in, Ga)Se2 (CIGS) solar cell', 'the 2017 International Conference on Telecommunications and Communication Engineering', 'ICTCE', 'Osaka', NULL, 'Jepang', '2017', 'Oktober', 'Int', 'ren', 'Tropical countries, such as Indonesia, need to consider the thread-off between high average solar irradiance throughout the year and the sporadic clouds due to the high rainfall in utilization of solar energy conversion Cu(In, Ga)Se2 (CIGS) with Polyimide substrate is known as one of the materials that produces significant power under low-light and cloudy condition. This 3rd generation solar cell is also promising for thin-film application. Due to Polyimide low thermal stability, a notch problem which significantly affected the current density (Jsc) arose. Single-graded flat-band structure was proven to be an option to solve this situation. In this research, further simulation was run to find the optimum design of this structure.', '12_seminar_the2017internationalconferenceontelecommunicationsandcommunicationengineering_c62ef43e.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.2., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2048, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(231, 12, 'Mak', 'Fabrication of CNT microarray for biosensor applications', 'The 7th Indonesia Japan Joint Scientific Symposium (IJJSS 2016)', 'Universitas Indonesia - Chiba University', 'Chiba', NULL, 'Jepang', '2016', 'November', 'Int', 'stin', 'Microarray technology has become one of the indispensable tools which can be used to identification of bio-molecules in cells, tissues, and disease, such as disease diagnosis, prediction, prevention, and drug discovery. The major advantages of the microarray biosensor are their ability of the simultaneous analysis of thousands parameters on a single platform and minimal sample consumption. Furthermore, carbon nanotubes (CNTs) with their outstanding properties are potential material for many applications including biosensors. To increase the fluorescence detection, the microarray will be established within the three-dimensional (3D) structure. The advantage of the 3D structure CNT for microarray platform is the enhancement of active surface area without sacrificing the size of the device. For instance, the external surface area of one CNT spot is roughly ~3.14×10-5 mm2. As arrays of 100 mm2 of CNT platform with 50 µm spacing, it can contain as many as 1.82 ×108 spots that is high-density microarrays. This high-density microarray is powerful tools for the screening of pharmaceuticals, investigation of biomolecule interactions and patient diagnostics. In this paper, the CNT is fabricated in microarray configuration to realize biochip sensor design. The CNT microarray was fabricated by using electron beam lithography for patterning microarray on silicon substrate, RF sputtering for deposit catalyst, and thermal plasma chemical vapor deposition (CVD) for growing vertically aligned CNT.', '12_seminar_the7thindonesiajapanjointscientificsymposiumijjss2016_c5881619.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(232, 12, 'Mak', 'Analysis of the Effect of the Amount of Lead Content in Perovskite Material as an Active Layer of So', '2th lnternational Conference on photonics Research', 'Interphotonics', 'Antalya', NULL, 'Turkey', '2019', 'November', 'Int', 'stin', 'Perovskite solar cells has reached 23.3% from 3.8% efficiency only in a few years range. The main material that used in perovskite solar cells are materials with perovskite structure as an active layer of those cells, such as methylammonium lead halide (CH3NH3PbI3). CH3NH3PbI3 perovskite contains inorganic compound lead chloride (PbCl2), which has high toxicity that can cause health hazards, such as damage to nervous systems, brain, cancer, etc. Many researches has shown further how the influence of lead chloride on health. However, there are currently no research that directly discusses about the effect of the amount of PbCl2 content on the electrical characteristics of CH3NH3PbI3 perovskite solar cell. This research discusses the effect of the amount of lead chloride on the electrical characteristics of perovskite solar cell.  Three perovskite solar cells were fabricated in this research which the active perovskite layer has varying amounts of PbCl2 content, namely 120 mg, 130 mg, and 140 mg. The results of the fabricated cells shows that the increase in the amount of PbCl2 content makes the CH3NH3PbI3 solar cells have better electrical characteristics. Cell with the best performance in this research is the cell with 140 mg amounts of PbCl2 content, with the value Voc = 0.879 V, Isc = 3.3 mA, FF = 0.47.', '12_seminar_2thlnternationalconferenceonphotonicsresearch_f7a54145.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(233, 4, 'Mak', 'Test', 'Test', 'Test', 'Test', NULL, 'Indonesia', '2022', 'Januari', 'Lok', 'ren', 'Test', '', 'W.4.1.4., W.4.1.5.', 2, 4, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, '2022-10-18 13:47:19', '2022-10-17 17:00:00'),
(234, 12, 'Mak', 'Modelling of Abrupt Junction HBT Using the Effect of Diffusion, Drift and Thermionic Emission Mechan', '8th International Symposium on Integrated Circuits, Devices & Systems (ISIC-99)', 'Nanyang Technology University', 'Singapore', NULL, 'Singapore', '1999', 'September', 'Int', 'ren', 'In abrupt junction there is discontinuity in the conduction and valence band and the energy level variation is much more that kT in a very small distance, therefore a model of abrupt junction Heterojuntion Bipolar Transistor (HBT) will be proposed. In this paper, the model which is used concerned the diffusion, drift and thermionic emission mechanism. Then, the model is applied to determine base current and collector current density of Si/Si0.75Ge0.25 HBT with base thickness 20, 30, 40, 50, 60 nm. The results show that the collector current density is increased and the base current density reduced since the base thickness have a tendecy more and more thin. By validiting of the model it has been seen that the value of collector and base current of this work had the same orde as those of Lopez and Kasper.', '12_seminar_8thinternationalsymposiumonintegratedcircuitsdevicessystemsisic99_f151e5c3.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2048, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
(235, 12, 'Mak', 'Performance silicon solar cell by using step graded Si0. 7Ge0. 3 layer', '5th International Photovoltaic Science & Engineering Conference', 'Shanghai Jiao Tong University', 'Shanghai', NULL, 'China', '2005', 'Oktober', 'Int', 'stin', 'The absorption of solar light at the silicon solar cell will be influenced by step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer. The Si0.7Ge0.3 layer will improve the absorption ability of silicon solar cell because it can extend the infrared response of a silicon solar cell and boost the current generation. The problem associated with this method is that, because the growth of Si0.7Ge0.3 layer on silicon layer cause misfit dislocation, it will also reduce the current generation. Due to this reason we use the step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer in order to reduce misfit dislocations. Those defects are the result on the lattice constant different between silicon and germanium. The step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer, which is used at silicon solar cell, is the 3 step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer with Si0.725Ge0.275 layer and Si0.72Ge0.28 layer growth on silicon layer, respectively before Si0.7Ge0.3 layer had been done. At this paper it was used simulation’s software, i.e. PC1D version 5.8 for examining and analyzing the effect of step graded Si0.7Ge0.3 layer at silicon solar cell. Parameters, we were investigated, were short circuit current, open circuit voltage, fill factor. Those three factors will affect the efficiency of silicon solar cell.', '12_seminar_5thinternationalphotovoltaicscienceengineeringconference_298bc755.pdf', 'W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.5., W.4.4.6., W.4.5.1., W.4.5.3.', 8, 32, 32, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8192, NULL, '2022-09-26 17:00:00', '2022-09-26 17:00:00'),
