(12, 10, 'pelatihan', 'Modelling an Inclusive Green Economy: An International Workshop ', 'United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) in collaboration with the Millennium Institute (MI) and ', 'Bergen', '', 'Norway', '2013', 'Mei', '', '', 'Lanjut', 'sd36', 'This workshop is part of PAGE initiatives that was formulated to follow on RIO+20. The partnership for Action on Green Economy (PAGE) drives a multi-stakeholder and participatory approach to create inclusive, sustainable societies.', '', 'W.2.1.1, W.2.1.2, W.2.1.5, W.2.2.1, W.2.2.2, W.2.2.3, W.4.1.1., W.4.1.2., W.4.1.3., W.4.1.4., W.4.1.5., W.4.4.1., W.4.4.2., W.4.4.3., W.4.4.4., W.4.4.6.', 16, 32, 48, 0, 768, 0, 768, 768, '2022-05-21 17:00:00', '2022-11-19 17:00:00'),
(13, 10, 'pelatihan', 'The 2nd International Workshop on Systems Modelling: System Analysis and Modelling for Green Economy', 'UKP4 (Presidential Working Unit for Supervision and Management of Development) and Sekolah Bisnis da', 'Jakarta Selatan', '', 'Indonesia', '2012', 'Mei', '', '', 'Lanjut', 'sd36', 'The main theme of workshop is System Analysis and Modelling for Green Economy . The research topics that will be discussed in this workshop deals with the national strategic policy, such as: 1. National Resource (fossil fuels, fish, water, forest, soil, etc) Efficiency and Development 2. Energy production (combustion) and emissions reduction 3. Pollution 4. Climate change mitigation and adaptation 5. Renewable energy systems 6. Socio-economic and environmental assessment of bio-energy systems MAIN SPEAKER Professor Dr. Pavel Kabat Director, International Institute for Applied Systems Analysis, Austria The main objectives of workshop can be described as follows: 1. Establishing the communication and cooperation among researchers, practitioners in system modelling and simulation especially in green economy area, both domestically and overseas. 2. Documenting research finding, consultation projects especially in green economy area that has been carried out by researchers from all over Indonesia and the world, especially by using system modelling and simulation for developing the policies. 3. Mapping the research finding and consultation projects especially in green economy area that can be implemented by decision makers in government', '', 'W.2.1.1, W.2.1.2, W.2.1.5, W.2.2.1, W.2.2.2, W.2.2.3, W.4.1.1., W.4.1.2., W.4.1.3., W.4.1.4., W.4.1.5.', 11, 22, 33, 0, 363, 0, 363, 363, '2022-05-21 17:00:00', '2022-10-10 17:00:00'),
